	(16,'4','2013-05-04 09:27:01',1,'2013-05-04 10:20:14','Benefits of Membership',1,'<h3>Receive the quarterly peer-reviewed publication, <em>Renal Nutrition Forum</em>.</h3><ul><li>Feature articles on a variety of nephrology nutrition issues enchance our knowledge and for continuing education.</li><li>Stipend reports contain conference summaries and highlights from members who have attended a conference in which RPG provided a stipend.</li><li>Relevant nutrition tips that can be shared with chronic kidney disease patients and their families.</li><li><strong>Plus much more&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</strong><br />Subscription for the membership year, begins with the Summer issue of the Forum, and continues through the Fall, Winter, and Spring Issues.<br />Contact the Membership Chairperson if you do not receive all issues.</li></ul><h3>Access to the new Professiona Resource Center (formerly the Lending Library).</h3><ul><li>Access to the new Professional Resource Center allows you to check out current texts and other materials free of charge except for the shipping costs. The library contains several of the texts that are recommended for review for the Certified Specialist in Renal Nutrition exam. We are constantly expanding and updating the library to include the latest resources.</li></ul><h3>Access to the members only area of RPG website, renalnutrition.org</h3><ul><li>Archives of the Renal Nutrition Forum</li><li>Clinical Articles of Interest</li><li>Patient Education Materials for purchase and download</li><li>Patient Education Handouts</li><li>Legislative, Reimbursement Resource</li></ul><h3>Are eligible to apply for stipends, scholarships, and grants.</h3><ul><li>For attending nephrology education conferences and meetings</li><li>For a scholarship worth $1,000.00 towards the pursuit of an advanced degree in nutrition.</li><li>For research in the field of nephrology nutrition</li><li>Eligibility begins after 1 year of RPG membership.<br />View scholarship and grant information. [add link]</li></ul><h3>Benefit from publications, which advance technical and clinical skills enhancing professional and patient education.</h3><ul><li>The Guidelines for Nutrition Care of Renal Patients</li><li>The Clinical Guide to Nutrition Care in End Stage Renal Disease, third edition (in progress)</li><li>Medical Nutrition Therapy Across the Continuum of Care</li></ul><h3>The RPG Dietetics Practice Group</h3><ul><li>Plans a scientific session on renal nutrition topics, suggested by RPG members, at the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics FNCE annual meeting.</li><li>Provides a collective voice to promote the interest of renal dietitians and affect change in policy and legislation.</li><li>Has an alliance with the National Kidney Foundation &ndash; Council on Renal Nutrition, to coordinate joint efforts and educational opportunities.</li><li>Provides an avenue through which RPG members can influence the future direction of The Academy through the Council on Practice.</li><li>Awards an &ldquo;Outstanding Service Award&rdquo;, to a member who has made significant contributions to the clinical practice and profession of renal nutrition.</li></ul>',4,'Receive the quarterly peer-reviewed publication, Renal Nutrition Forum.\r\n\r\nFeature articles on a variety of nephrology nutrition issues enchance our knowledge and for continuing education.\r\nStipend reports contain conference summaries and highlights from members who have attended a conference in which RPG provided a stipend.\r\nRelevant nutrition tips that can be shared with chronic kidney disease patients and their families.\r\nPlus much more&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.Subscription for the membership year, begins with the Summer issue of the Forum, and continues through the Fall, Winter, and Spring Issues.Contact the Membership Chairperson if you do not receive all issues.\r\n\r\nAccess to the new Professiona Resource Center (formerly the Lending Library).\r\n\r\nAccess to the new Professional Resource Center allows you to check out current texts and other materials free of charge except for the shipping costs. The library contains several of the texts that are recommended for review for the Certified Specialist in Renal Nutrition exam. We are constantly expanding and updating the library to include the latest resources.\r\n\r\nAccess to the members only area of RPG website, renalnutrition.org\r\n\r\nArchives of the Renal Nutrition Forum\r\nClinical Articles of Interest\r\nPatient Education Materials for purchase and download\r\nPatient Education Handouts\r\nLegislative, Reimbursement Resource\r\n\r\nAre eligible to apply for stipends, scholarships, and grants.\r\n\r\nFor attending nephrology education conferences and meetings\r\nFor a scholarship worth $1,000.00 towards the pursuit of an advanced degree in nutrition.\r\nFor research in the field of nephrology nutrition\r\nEligibility begins after 1 year of RPG membership.View scholarship and grant information. [add link]\r\n\r\nBenefit from publications, which advance technical and clinical skills enhancing professional and patient education.\r\n\r\nThe Guidelines for Nutrition Care of Renal Patients\r\nThe Clinical Guide to Nutrition Care in End Stage Renal Disease, third edition (in progress)\r\nMedical Nutrition Therapy Across the Continuum of Care\r\n\r\nThe RPG Dietetics Practice Group\r\n\r\nPlans a scientific session on renal nutrition topics, suggested by RPG members, at the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics FNCE annual meeting.\r\nProvides a collective voice to promote the interest of renal dietitians and affect change in policy and legislation.\r\nHas an alliance with the National Kidney Foundation &ndash; Council on Renal Nutrition, to coordinate joint efforts and educational opportunities.\r\nProvides an avenue through which RPG members can influence the future direction of The Academy through the Council on Practice.\r\nAwards an &ldquo;Outstanding Service Award&rdquo;, to a member who has made significant contributions to the clinical practice and profession of renal nutrition.\r\n','Benefits of Membership','benefits-of-membership'),
	(17,'4','2013-05-04 10:01:08',1,'2013-05-04 10:12:10','About Renal Dietitians (RPG)',1,'<h3>Mission</h3><p>Empowering members to be the nation\'s leaders in nephrology nutrition.</p><h3>Vision</h3><p>RPG members are a valued source of expertise in nephrology nutrition.</p><h3>Strategic Plan 2012 - 2017</h3><ol><li>To be a premiere source of nephrology nutrition<br />a. Provide relevant clinical resources, valued initiative and programs to engage a diverse membership<br />b. Enhance and promote the development of innovative resources for membership<br />c. Support members in professional development endeavors and career ladder progression</li><li>Adapt and respond to current and future societal trends impacting the nephrology community<br />a. Embrace new technologies for communication and education<br />b. Provide resources to encompass changing societal demographics and improve our membership\'s cultural and behavior change competencies</li><li>Promote advocacy of nephrology nutrition issues<br />a. Advocate for nephrology nutrition issues<br />b. Support research and resources impacting nephrology nutrition<br />c. Develop relationships with organizations to maximize collaborations on nephrology related concerns<br />d. Inform and engage our membership on public policy issues impacting nephrology</li></ol>',4,'Mission\r\nEmpowering members to be the nation\'s leaders in nephrology nutrition.\r\nVision\r\nRPG members are a valued source of expertise in nephrology nutrition.\r\nStrategic Plan 2012 - 2017\r\n\r\nTo be a premiere source of nephrology nutritiona. Provide relevant clinical resources, valued initiative and programs to engage a diverse membershipb. Enhance and promote the development of innovative resources for membershipc. Support members in professional development endeavors and career ladder progression\r\nAdapt and respond to current and future societal trends impacting the nephrology communitya. Embrace new technologies for communication and educationb. Provide resources to encompass changing societal demographics and improve our membership\'s cultural and behavior change competencies\r\nPromote advocacy of nephrology nutrition issuesa. Advocate for nephrology nutrition issuesb. Support research and resources impacting nephrology nutritionc. Develop relationships with organizations to maximize collaborations on nephrology related concernsd. Inform and engage our membership on public policy issues impacting nephrology\r\n','About RPG','about-renal-dietitians-rpg'),
	(18,'4','2013-05-04 11:17:52',1,'2013-05-04 11:22:57','Join or Renew RPG Membership',1,'<h3>How Do I Join?</h3><p>If you are an Academy member, <strong><a href=\"http://www.eatright.org\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong>. You will be taken to the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics website where you can login to your profile and join RPG online. Once logged-in, look at your membership account information and add the Renal Dietitians (RPG) as a DPG.</p><p align=\"center\">You also can call the Academy at (800/877-1600 ext. 5000) to join today.</p><p>The membership year runs from June 1 through May 31. The Academy accepts payment for the current year through the end of January. Once you have joined, the Academy will inform RPG and you will start receiving your emails and mailings. Any printed issues missed (from the current membership year) of the Renal Nutrition Forum willl be mailed to you.</p><h3>Renew Renal Dietitians (RPG) Membership</h3><p>The membership year runs from June 1 through May 31. The Academy accepts payment for the current year through the end of February. Once you have joined, ANAD will inform us and you will start receiving your mailings. All back issues of newsletters will be mailed to you.</p><ul><li>Online<br />To pay dues: <strong><a href=\"http://www.eatright.org/dues\" target=\"_blank\">www.eatright.org/dues</a></strong><br />To join online: <strong><a href=\"http://www.eatright.org/myada/join/find.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">www.eatright.org/myada/join/find.aspx</a></strong></li><li>By Phone<br />Contact the Academy&rsquo;s Member Service Center at 1-800-877-1600 ext. 5000.</li></ul>',4,'How Do I Join?\r\nIf you are an Academy member, click here. You will be taken to the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics website where you can login to your profile and join RPG online. Once logged-in, look at your membership account information and add the Renal Dietitians (RPG) as a DPG.\r\nYou also can call the Academy at (800/877-1600 ext. 5000) to join today.\r\nThe membership year runs from June 1 through May 31. The Academy accepts payment for the current year through the end of January. Once you have joined, the Academy will inform RPG and you will start receiving your emails and mailings. Any printed issues missed (from the current membership year) of the Renal Nutrition Forum willl be mailed to you.\r\nRenew Renal Dietitians (RPG) Membership\r\nThe membership year runs from June 1 through May 31. The Academy accepts payment for the current year through the end of February. Once you have joined, ANAD will inform us and you will start receiving your mailings. All back issues of newsletters will be mailed to you.\r\n\r\nOnlineTo pay dues: www.eatright.org/duesTo join online: www.eatright.org/myada/join/find.aspx\r\nBy PhoneContact the Academy&rsquo;s Member Service Center at 1-800-877-1600 ext. 5000.\r\n','How to Join RPG or Renew RPG Membership','join-or-renew-rpg-membership'),
