	(21,'4','2013-05-09 01:20:12',1,'2013-05-09 01:43:28','Public Policy, MNT & HOD Updates ',1,'<p>More general reimbursement resources in links/resources area. [link]</p><h3>Online Interactive Tools</h3><p>The Academy\'s Evidence Analysis Library and the Academy&rsquo;s Evidence-Based Nutrition Practice Guideline Toolkits: <a href=\"http://www.adaevidencelibrary.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.adaevidencelibrary.com/</a></p><p>The Academy\'s Reimbursement Community of Interest (COI) is an interactive online tool that is available to Academy members who desire to learn more about coverage for medical nutrition therapy (MNT) and exchange best practices to help advance coverage of nutrition services with <a href=\"http://www.eatright.org/Members/content.aspx?id=7490\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.eatright.org/Members/content.aspx?id=7490</a></p><h3>House of Delegates (HOD) Updates</h3><p><a href=\"/files/uploads/HODFall2012FactSheet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">RPG HOD Fall 2012 Fact Sheet</a><br /><a href=\"/files/uploads/HODFall2012FactSheet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">(Council on Future Practice Visioning Report: Moving Forward-A Vision for Education, Credentialing, and Practice)</a></p><h3>The MNT Provider Newsletter</h3><p>The MNT Provider newsletter is an essential practice management resource for registered dietitians.<a href=\"http://www.eatright.org/mntprovider\" target=\"_blank\"> http://www.eatright.org/mntprovider</a></p><ul><li><a href=\"/files/uploads/RPGMNTProvider-April2013.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">MNT Provider current issue: MNT April 2013 Issue</a></li><li>MNT Provider Newsletter Archives - Click here [link]</li></ul><h3>The Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics MNT Information</h3><p><a href=\"/staff/files/uploads/CMS_Updates_ICD-9-CM_dx_codes_2007.doc\" target=\"_blank\">Updated ICD-9 codes </a>- Excerpt from the Academy Medicare MNT Provider Newsletter<br />The MNT Provider newsletter is a free resource for all the Academy members. It has information on Medicare, private insurance, practice management and more. Read it each month at <a href=\"http://www.eatright.org/mntprovider\" target=\"_blank\">www.eatright.org/mntprovider.</a></p><h3>CMS Issues Final 2011 Payment Policies For Medicare Advantage and Prescription Drug Plans</h3><p>The Rate Announcement also contains the following key changes in response to this new legislation: Click Here</p><p>In addition to changes resulting from new legislation, the following key changes or updates have been made to the Advance Notice and draft Call Letter in response to public comments received from beneficiary advocacy groups, associations, Congressional agencies, members of the public, and health plans: Click Here</p><p>The Final Rate Announcement and Call Letter can be viewed at: <a href=\"http://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Health-Plans/MedicareAdvtgSpecRateStats/index.html?redirect=/MedicareAdvtgSpecRateStats/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cms.hhs.gov/MedicareAdvtgSpecRateStats/</a> .</p><h3>Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics Legislative Contacts</h3><table style=\"width: 690px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"4\" cellpadding=\"4\" align=\"center\"><tbody><tr align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><td width=\"220\">Congressional &amp; Political Affairs</td><td width=\"220\">Jeanne Blankenship</td><td width=\"250\"><a href=\"mailto:Govaffairs@eatright.org\">Govaffairs@eatright.org</a></td></tr><tr align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><td>Strategic Policy/ Partnerships <br /> Regulatory Affairs</td><td><p>Mary Pat Raimondi<br /> Pepin Tuma</p></td><td><a href=\"mailto:Govaffairs@eatright.org\">Govaffairs@eatright.org </a></td></tr><tr align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><td>Communications Manager</td><td>Jessica Larson</td><td><a href=\"mailto:Govaffairs@eatright.org\">Govaffairs@eatright.org</a></td></tr><tr align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><td>Consumer Protection</td><td>Juliana Smith</td><td><a href=\"mailto:Govaffairs@eatright.org\">Govaffairs@eatright.org</a></td></tr><tr align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><td>Informa