	(38,'4','2013-05-10 10:25:01',1,'2013-05-11 08:18:52','Sponsors',1,'<p>Thank you to our current sponsors! If yo u are interested in becoming an RPG sponsor, please go to the <a href=\"/content/sponsorship-opportunities.html\">Sponsorship Opportunities</a> page.</p><h3>Current Sponsors</h3><p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://abbottnutrition.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"vertical-align: middle;\" title=\"Abbott Nutrition\" src=\"/files/images/abbott_nutrition.jpg\" alt=\"Abbott Nutrition\" /></a></p><h4 align=\"center\">&nbsp;<a href=\"http://abbottnutrition.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Abbott Nutrition</a></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.fmcna.com/fmcna/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><img title=\"Fresenius Medical Care\" src=\"/files/images/fresenui_medical_care.jpg\" alt=\"Fresenius Medical Care\" /></a></p><h4 align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.fmcna.com/fmcna/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Fresenius Medical Care</a></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>',4,'Thank you to our current sponsors! If yo u are interested in becoming an RPG sponsor, please go to the Sponsorship Opportunities page.\r\nCurrent Sponsors\r\n\r\n&nbsp;Abbott Nutrition\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFresenius Medical Care\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;','sponsorship, sponsor, advertiser, adverstisng','sponsors'),
	(39,'4','2013-05-11 07:56:43',1,'2013-05-11 09:35:07','Sponsorship Opportunities',1,'<h3>Current Print Ad Rates for the Renal Nutrition Forum</h3><p>The <em><strong>Renal Nutrition Forum (RNF)</strong></em>is a quarterly peer-reviewed publication of the Renal Dietitians Practice Group of the American Dietetic Association. It reaches approximately 2500 renal and related nutrition professional members every issue. These nephrology and nutrition professionals influence the nutrition management and care of patients and clients in all stages of chronic kidney disease. They utilize their expertise and skills in many different settings which may include: hospitals, specialty clinics, outpatient clinics, and private practice and interact with primary care physicians, nephrologists, nurses and other medical professionals every day.</p><p>The <em><strong>Renal Nutrition Forum</strong></em> has been a vital tool for renal professionals and patients since 1980. It is an excellent publication venue for advertising the products of your company to focus on the target audience. It&rsquo;s the &ldquo;Go To&rdquo; publication for the latest in clinical, patient and product information when it comes to managing chronic kidney disease, diabetes, cardiovascular disease, etc.</p><h3>Do you want to advertise on the RPG website?</h3><p>Please contact <a href=\"mailto:helpU@renalnutrition.org\">helpU@renalnutrition.org</a> for more information. RPG is creating some new exciting sponsorship opportunities on their new website.</p><p><strong>For Additional Information</strong><br />Emily Cutler, MS, RD, Advertising Editor<br />Renal Nutrition Forum<br /><a href=\"mailto:emilycreamer@aol.com\">emilycreamer@aol.com</a></p>',4,'Current Print Ad Rates for the Renal Nutrition Forum\r\nThe Renal Nutrition Forum (RNF)is a quarterly peer-reviewed publication of the Renal Dietitians Practice Group of the American Dietetic Association. It reaches approximately 2500 renal and related nutrition professional members every issue. These nephrology and nutrition professionals influence the nutrition management and care of patients and clients in all stages of chronic kidney disease. They utilize their expertise and skills in many different settings which may include: hospitals, specialty clinics, outpatient clinics, and private practice and interact with primary care physicians, nephrologists, nurses and other medical professionals every day.\r\nThe Renal Nutrition Forum has been a vital tool for renal professionals and patients since 1980. It is an excellent publication venue for advertising the products of your company to focus on the target audience. It&rsquo;s the &ldquo;Go To&rdquo; publication for the latest in clinical, patient and product information when it comes to managing chronic kidney disease, diabetes, cardiovascular disease, etc.\r\nDo you want to advertise on the RPG website?\r\nPlease contact helpU@renalnutrition.org for more information. RPG is creating some new exciting sponsorship opportunities on their new website.\r\nFor Additional InformationEmily Cutler, MS, RD, Advertising EditorRenal Nutrition Forumemilycreamer@aol.com','sponsors, sponsorship opportunities, advertising, advertiser','sponsorship-opportunities'),
	(40,'4','2013-05-11 10:52:54',1,'2013-05-11 10:53:52','Board',1,'<p>For the board members\' contact information, you must login to the <strong><a href=\"/about-rpg/rpg-board-contact-information.html\">members area</a></strong>. [link]&nbsp;</p><h3><a name=\"chair\"></a>Officers</h3><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Chair\" src=\"/files/images/Sarah_Kruger_106x133.jpg\" alt=\"Sarah Kruger, MS, RD, CSR\" />Sarah Kruger, MS, RD, CSR<br />Chair</h4><p>Sarah has a BS from Michigan State University and a MS from Case Western Reserve University, both in nutrition. She is currently a CKD Sales Specialist for Abbott Renal Care. Sarah has experience working at Renal Advantage Inc and started her own practice consulting CKD stage 3/4 patients. Sarah is also involved with other professional organizations including Chair for Michigan CRN.<a name=\"pastchair\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Immediate Past Chair\" src=\"/files/images/rachel_m.jpg\" alt=\"Rachel R Majorowicz, RD, LD\" />Rachael R Majorowicz, RD, LD<br />Immediate Past Chair</h4><p>Rachael has worked at Mayo Clinic outpatient hemodialysis providing patient care, creating educational materials, and providing nutrition education for medical students, nephrology fellows, nurses, and dietetic interns. She remains active in CRN-Minnesota planning numerous educational events for renal professionals and promoting patient programs.<a name=\"chairelect\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Chair-Elect\" src=\"/files/images/mary_kay_hensley_new.jpg\" alt=\"Mary Kay Hensley, MS, RD, CSR\" />Mary Kay Hensley, MS, RD, CSR<br />Chair-Elect</h4><p>Mary Kay Hensley has provided renal nutrition therapy for many years starting in Nebraska &amp; then in Indiana (IN). She is employed by Davita, Inc. in IN. She has served as the NKF-CRN Chair. She was instrumental in the launch of JREN during her tenure &amp; served on the first editorial board. She serves on the Board of Directors for NKF of Indiana &amp; is a past-President. She is an active member of the International Congress of Renal Nutrition &amp; Metabolism. Mary Kay served on the Academy Specialty Practice Board and was a member of the work group to develop the Renal Specialty Certification exam.<a name=\"sec\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Secretary\" src=\"/files/images/RPGJoAnnR_sm.jpg\" alt=\"JoAnn Randazzo, RD, CDN\" />JoAnn Randazzo, RD, CDN<br />Secretary</h4><p>JoAnn is employed as an outpatient dialysis dietitian and co-owner of a private practice, with a primary focus on corporate wellness programs. She is currently pursuing completion of her Master\'s Degree. In addition to being a member of the Academy of Nutrition &amp; Dietetics, she is affiliated with CRN-LI and the NYSDA. JoAnn is looking forward to being a Board Member of the Renal Dietitians Practice Group.<a name=\"treas\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Treasurer, Renal Nutrition Forum\" src=\"/files/images/stacey_phillips.gif\" alt=\"Stacey C. Phillips, RD, LD\" />Stacey C. Phillips, RD, LD<br />Treasurer, Renal Nutrition Forum</h4><p>Stacey is excited to continue on the RPG EC committee in the role of treasurer. She has been a dietitian for the last seven years and gets to work with patients in early CKD to transplantation. One of the highlights of being involved with RPG has been getting to know other dietitians and promoting our profession.<a name=\"hod\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"HOD Member\" src=\"/files/images/RPG-Pam-Kent_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Pamela Kent\" />Pamela Kent<br />HOD Member</h4><p>Pam has been a renal dietitian for over 25 years. She has been an invited speaker at regional &amp; national conferences. Her publications include articles and book chapters focusing on obesity, medical nutrition therapy, IDPN, DM, liver disease, CKD and acute kidney injury. Pam has held several positions within RPG including Chair, Treasurer and Editor. In addition, she is the past NKF-CRN Spring Clinical Meetings Chair.<a name=\"media\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Website &amp; Editorial Board</h3><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Electronic Media Manager\" src=\"/files/images/cathy_g_m.jpg\" alt=\"Cathy M. Goeddke-Merickel, MS, RD, LD\" />Cathy M. Goeddeke-Merickel, MS, RD, LD<br />Electronic Media Manager</h4><p>Cathy is a Nephrology Dietitian &amp; Independent Clinical Consultant. She has clinical &amp; research experience in diabetes, obesity, CKD stages 1-5. She was a member of the Committee for Standards of Practice and Standards of Professional Performance for Nephrology Care; published in JADA &amp; JREN. Cathy has authored peer-reviewed journal articles, book chapters &amp; is an an invited speaker on topics such as botanical medicine, CKD diabetes, obesity/weight management, low literacy education &amp; nutrition/wellness. She has been a contributor for professional and patient education publications. She enjoys doing anything active outdoors!<a name=\"forumeditor\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Forum Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\" src=\"/files/images/Sara_Erickson.jpg\" alt=\"Sara Erickson RD, CSR, LDN, CNSC\" />Sara Erickson RD, CSR, LDN, CNSC<br />Forum Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum</h4><p>Sara is the Pediatric Renal Dietitian for Levine Children&rsquo;s Hospital and Specialty Center in Charlotte, NC. She has worked in pediatrics for over 10 years &amp; transitioned to pediatric nephrology 2 yrs ago where she manages the nutrition care of patients at an outpatient clinic, dialysis unit, and transplant program. She received her BS from the U of North Carolina &ndash; Greensboro and completed her internship at East Carolina University at New Hanover Regional Medical Center in Wilmington, NC.<a name=\"coeditorone\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Co-Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\" src=\"/files/images/amy_tarpey_new.jpg\" alt=\"Amy Tarpey\" />Amy Tarpey<br />Co-Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum</h4><p>Amy is employed as a renal nutrition sales executive at Pentec Health and has had a small private practice for patients with CKD stages 1-4 since 2004. Previously, she worked as a renal dietitian in acute care, chronic ambulatory, nutrition support and research settings. She received a BA in Psychology from the U of Arizona and an MS in Nutritional Science from California State University, Long Beach. She is looking forward to a new challenge as part of the Renal Nutrition Forum Editorial team, but hopes she will still have time for her long runs.<a name=\"coeditortwo\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Co-Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\" src=\"/files/images/Jackie_Tremont.jpg\" alt=\"Jackie Termont\" />Jackie Termont<br />Co-Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum</h4><p>Jackie has been a renal dietitian for DaVita Dialysis in Richmond, VA since 2008. Originally from Indiana, she earned her undergraduate degree in dietetics at Purdue University. She previously worked for a small hospital in southern Michigan before moving with her husband to Richmond. She was the co-chair for the Virginia CRN and has recently accepted the position of the RNF Co-Editor. She still finds time to bake which makes her co-workers very happy!<a name=\"advertising\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Advertising Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\" src=\"/files/images/Emily_Cutler.jpg\" alt=\"Emily Cutler, MS, RD, LDN\" />Emily Cutler, MS, RD, LDN<br />Adversting Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum</h4><p>She has experience working with nutrition support, renal nutrition, and health/wellness. She enjoys educating &amp; caring for dialysis patients, while working in outpatient dialysis (FMS) on Chicago\'s southside. She recently worked at a facility with a focus on nutrition support/critical illness, and continued to educate and care for CKD and HD patients. In addition to renal nutrition, she continues to pursue a passion of promoting health and wellness. She loves to cook, run, travel, and spend time with her husband and toddler daughter.<a name=\"membership\"></a></p><p><br /><br /></p><h3>Committee Chairs</h3><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Membership Outreach Chair\" src=\"/files/images/Nilma_Desai_103x125.jpg\" alt=\"Nilma Desai, MS, BS, RD\" />Nilma Desai, MS, BS, RD<br />Membership Outreach Chair</h4><p>Nilma received her B.S. in Nutrition and Dietetics from California State University, Long Beach and M.S. in Public Health Nutrition degree from Loma Linda University. She has over 6 years of experience in renal nutrition working for Abbott Pharmaceuticals and DaVita dialysis center. She currently works as a consulting dietitian counseling CKD Stage 3/4 patients and writes continuing education modules for Gannett Education. She also previously served on the Ex Boards for the Southern California NKF and CRN.<a name=\"webinar\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Webinar Chair\" src=\"/files/images/annamarie_rodriguez.jpg\" alt=\"Annamarie Rodriguez\" />Annamarie Rodriguez<br />Webinar Chair</h4><p>Annamarie is employed by Sanofi Renal as a Renal Clinical consultant. Her work experience encompasses renal nutrition and pharmaceuticals in both sales, education and as an account manager with oral/injectable drug therapies and IDPN. She has served in a variety of committees with local NKF and CRN chapters in San Antonio and currently in WI, and is presently serving as chair for WI CRN. Personal interests include football, gardening, volunteer activities, cooking, antiquing and \'one day\' will learn to speak Spanish and play the violin.<a name=\"social\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Social Media Chair\" src=\"/files/images/RPG-Sarah-Coffin_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Sarah Coffin\" />Sarah Coffin<br />Social Media Chair</h4><p>Sarah Coffin career began as a hospital dietitian in La Jolla Ca, and transitioned into 15+ years of renal nutrition at various dialysis clinics, and nutrition instructor at local colleges. She later expanded into pharmaceutical sales with Abbott Renal Care. With Coffin\'s motivation to help and educate others about the importance of nutrition, she is currently teaching at Palomar College, a health writer for Gannett Education, and has served on various educational symposia committees with the NKF &amp; CRN of Southern California.<a name=\"project\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Project Chair\" src=\"/files/images/Meg_McCartney.jpg\" alt=\"Meg McCartney, RD, LDN\" />Meg McCartney, RD, LDN<br />Project Chair</h4><p>For the past five years, Meg has found her niche in renal nutrition, where she enjoys bridging the clinical and relational aspects of dialysis care for patients. Prior to that, her experience was in nutrition support and hospital food service, after earning her BS from Michigan State University. She has also been involved with the Chicago Dietetics Association and volunteering for NKF in Chicago.<a name=\"kidney\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Kidney Friendly Food Shelf Chair\" src=\"/files/images/RPGLindseyZ.jpg\" alt=\"Lindsey Zirker RD, LD\" />Lindsey Zirker RD, LD<br />Kidney Friendly Food Shelf Chair</h4><p>Lindsey has a BS from Brigham Young University. She has a varied background with experience in eating disorders, research/development, health/wellness programs, and teaching community cooking and nutrition classes. She currently works at an outpatient dialysis clinic with hemo and peritoneal dialysis patients. Lindsey has served on the NKF Education Committee and as the Chair for the West Division Regional Dietitian Conference for Liberty Dialysis.<a name=\"website\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Website Reviewer Subcommittee Chair\" src=\"/files/images/erin_nelson_new.jpg\" alt=\"Erin Nelson\" />Erin Nelson<br />Website Reviewer Subcommittee Chair</h4><p>Erin earned her B.S. in Nutritional Sciences from Texas A&amp;M University and completed her internship &amp; M.S. of Public Health in Health Promotion &amp; Behavioral Sciences from the U of Texas School of Public Health. She currently works for Aramark at St. Luke\'s Episcopal Hospital. She has been working with Kidney &amp; Pancreas Transplant patients since 2009. Prior to that she covered general medicine patients and previously served on the Houston Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics Board of Directors.<a name=\"ipad\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"iPad Subcommittee Chair\" src=\"/files/images/MelissaPrest.jpg\" alt=\"Melissa Prest\" />Melissa Prest<br />iPad Subcommittee Chair</h4><p>Melissa has her MS in Clinical Nutrition from the University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey. Her thesis research focused on nutrition assessment in hemodialysis patients. She has worked in clinical dietetics with a focus on cardiology &amp; rehab/diabetes/physical rehab, &amp; long-term care. For the past 4 yrs she has provided MNT therapy for in-center hemodialysis &amp; peritoneal dialysis patients. Melissa is an active board member for NKF-CRN Illinois chapter &amp; local dietetic association.<a name=\"handout\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Handouts Subcommittee Chair\" src=\"/files/images/Rita_Milam_new.jpg\" alt=\"Rita Milam\" />Rita Milam<br />Handouts Subcommittee Chair</h4><p>Rita is a clinical dietitian at Central Arkansas Veterans Healthcare System. She works with the MOVE weight management program &amp; veterans with CKD on hemodialysis &amp; peritoneal dialysis. Previously she was a renal dietitian in a local dialysis clinic &amp; started her career as a clinical dietitian after completing her dietetic internship. She has a Masters of Arts in English-technical and expository writing. Rita enjoys cooking, flower gardening, &amp; traveling with her husband and 3 dogs.<a name=\"prc\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Professional Resource Center Coordinator\" src=\"/files/images/nadiya.gif\" alt=\"Nadiya Lakhani\" />Nadiya Lakhani<br />Professional Resource Center Coordinator</h4><p>Nadiya graduated from UT Southwestern Medical Center in Dallas and found her passion in renal nutrition. She is working for FMC and also works as a Clinical Dietitian for HCA hospitals and as a Private Consultant in the community. Nadiya recently assisted with a study for Protocol Management with Dallas Nephrology Associates. Nadiya has been a Legislative Co-Chair for Dallas Dietetic Association, actively involved with NKF Spring Seminar and is currently serving as the Chair for North Texas CRN.<a name=\"public\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Public Policy/MNT Chair\" src=\"/files/images/RPG-Sarah-Mott_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Sarah Mott, MS, RD, LDN\" />Sarah Mott MS, RD, LDN<br />Public Policy/MNT Chair</h4><p>Sarah has spent 6 years working in outpatient dialysis clinics and provided care for in-center hemodialysis, peritoneal dialysis, and home hemodialysis patients. She received her BS degree from Central Michigan University and her MS from Mount Mary College. Sarah is now working towards a Master\'s in Public Health at the University of Michigan with a focus on health management &amp; policy. Sarah is currently serving as a National Kidney Disease Education Program Coordinating Panel member.<a name=\"awards\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Awards/Scholarship Chair\" src=\"/files/images/sandy_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Sandy McDonald-Hangach, RD\" />Sandy McDonald-Hangach, RD<br />Awards/Scholarshp Chair</h4><p>Sandy is currently employed at Davita . She works at 2 facilities in Detroit Mich and has been a Renal Dietitian for the past 12 yrs. She belongs to the following professional organizations Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics, RPG, CRN of Michigan, and Southeastern Michigan Dietetic Association, and MDA. When she is not working or volunteering for professional organizations she travels, exercises, reads, eats out, shops, attends movies and spends time with family &amp; friends!<a name=\"mentor\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>OPEN POSITION<br />Mentor Chair<a name=\"nominatingone\"></a></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Nominating Chair\" src=\"/files/images/RPG-Elizabeth-Neumann_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Elizabeth Neumann\" />Elizabeth Neumann<br />Nominating Chair</h4><p>Elizabeth Neumann has been an outpatient Renal Dietitian at US Renal Care for the past 5 years. She covers 3 clinics &amp; manages the nutritional care of over 100 patients. She serves as Treasurer for CRN-Fort Worth &amp; is past President of Fort Worth Dietitic Association. Her work experience includes pediatrics, geriatrics, pharmaceutical sales and Clinical Instructor at the U of Texas Dental School. She is an avid scuba diver, gardener and snow skier.<a name=\"nominatingtwo\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Nominating Chair\" src=\"/files/images/RPG-Valerie-Hannah_sm.jpg\" alt=\"Valarie Hannah\" />Valarie Hannahs<br />Nominating Member</h4><p>Valarie has worked in renal since 2007 as an outpatient renal dietitian &amp; now as the Corporate Manager of Renal Nutrition with American Renal Associates. She earned her B.S. in Medical Dietetics from Ohio State University and M.S. in Exercise Science &amp; Health Promotion from California University of Pennsylvania. Valarie is a member of RPG, &amp; SCAN and NKF &amp; CRN of Ohio. Motivating dietitians to be more involved &amp; creating educational opportunities are a few of the many goals she hopes to achieve with RPG. Valarie also provides nutrition counseling &amp; in her spare time competes in a variety of outdoor events.<a name=\"nominatingthree\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Betty Parry Fisher, MS, RD<br />Nominating Member</h4><p>Bio coming soon...</p><h4><a name=\"academy\"></a></h4><p><br /><br /></p><h3>Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics</h3><h4><img style=\"float: left; margin-left: 4px; margin-right: 4px;\" title=\"Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics Team\" src=\"/files/images/susan.jpg\" alt=\"Susan Dupraw, MPH, RD\" />Susan Dupraw, MPH, RD<br />Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics Manager, Practice Team</h4><p>Susan works on the Practice Team at the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics in Chicago, IL. My role at the Academy is to promote and assist in coordinating activities of five dietetic practice groups. My previous positions included clinical nutrition, nutrition education and nutrition marketing.</p>',4,'For the board members\' contact information, you must login to the members area. [link]&nbsp;\r\nOfficers\r\nSarah Kruger, MS, RD, CSRChair\r\nSarah has a BS from Michigan State University and a MS from Case Western Reserve University, both in nutrition. She is currently a CKD Sales Specialist for Abbott Renal Care. Sarah has experience working at Renal Advantage Inc and started her own practice consulting CKD stage 3/4 patients. Sarah is also involved with other professional organizations including Chair for Michigan CRN.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nRachael R Majorowicz, RD, LDImmediate Past Chair\r\nRachael has worked at Mayo Clinic outpatient hemodialysis providing patient care, creating educational materials, and providing nutrition education for medical students, nephrology fellows, nurses, and dietetic interns. She remains active in CRN-Minnesota planning numerous educational events for renal professionals and promoting patient programs.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nMary Kay Hensley, MS, RD, CSRChair-Elect\r\nMary Kay Hensley has provided renal nutrition therapy for many years starting in Nebraska &amp; then in Indiana (IN). She is employed by Davita, Inc. in IN. She has served as the NKF-CRN Chair. She was instrumental in the launch of JREN during her tenure &amp; served on the first editorial board. She serves on the Board of Directors for NKF of Indiana &amp; is a past-President. She is an active member of the International Congress of Renal Nutrition &amp; Metabolism. Mary Kay served on the Academy Specialty Practice Board and was a member of the work group to develop the Renal Specialty Certification exam.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nJoAnn Randazzo, RD, CDNSecretary\r\nJoAnn is employed as an outpatient dialysis dietitian and co-owner of a private practice, with a primary focus on corporate wellness programs. She is currently pursuing completion of her Master\'s Degree. In addition to being a member of the Academy of Nutrition &amp; Dietetics, she is affiliated with CRN-LI and the NYSDA. JoAnn is looking forward to being a Board Member of the Renal Dietitians Practice Group.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nStacey C. Phillips, RD, LDTreasurer, Renal Nutrition Forum\r\nStacey is excited to continue on the RPG EC committee in the role of treasurer. She has been a dietitian for the last seven years and gets to work with patients in early CKD to transplantation. One of the highlights of being involved with RPG has been getting to know other dietitians and promoting our profession.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nPamela KentHOD Member\r\nPam has been a renal dietitian for over 25 years. She has been an invited speaker at regional &amp; national conferences. Her publications include articles and book chapters focusing on obesity, medical nutrition therapy, IDPN, DM, liver disease, CKD and acute kidney injury. Pam has held several positions within RPG including Chair, Treasurer and Editor. In addition, she is the past NKF-CRN Spring Clinical Meetings Chair.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nWebsite &amp; Editorial Board\r\nCathy M. Goeddeke-Merickel, MS, RD, LDElectronic Media Manager\r\nCathy is a Nephrology Dietitian &amp; Independent Clinical Consultant. She has clinical &amp; research experience in diabetes, obesity, CKD stages 1-5. She was a member of the Committee for Standards of Practice and Standards of Professional Performance for Nephrology Care; published in JADA &amp; JREN. Cathy has authored peer-reviewed journal articles, book chapters &amp; is an an invited speaker on topics such as botanical medicine, CKD diabetes, obesity/weight management, low literacy education &amp; nutrition/wellness. She has been a contributor for professional and patient education publications. She enjoys doing anything active outdoors!\r\n&nbsp;\r\nSara Erickson RD, CSR, LDN, CNSCForum Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\r\nSara is the Pediatric Renal Dietitian for Levine Children&rsquo;s Hospital and Specialty Center in Charlotte, NC. She has worked in pediatrics for over 10 years &amp; transitioned to pediatric nephrology 2 yrs ago where she manages the nutrition care of patients at an outpatient clinic, dialysis unit, and transplant program. She received her BS from the U of North Carolina &ndash; Greensboro and completed her internship at East Carolina University at New Hanover Regional Medical Center in Wilmington, NC.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nAmy TarpeyCo-Editor, Renal Nutrition Forum\r\nAmy is employed as a renal nutrition sales executive at Pentec Health and has had a small private practice for 